<br>
Appreciation, Credit and Thanks to the post:<br>
<br>
&quot;Consider Messages for Monsters and NPC's&quot; from everquest.allakhazam.com/<br>
<br>
<br>
Social Scale <br>
(Rank, Message)<br>
<br>
+4, Ally (Fondly was used back in the dark ages of EQ, but was removed. Now it's back under the Ally term) <br>
+3, warmly <br>
+2, kindly <br>
+1, amiably <br>
0, indifferently <br>
-1, apprehensively <br>
-2, dubiously <br>
-3, threateningly <br>
-4, ready to attack <br>
<br>
Threat Scale <br>
(Your Target's level difference to you, Consider color, message)<br>
<br>
The /con message varies depending upon your level. It changes depending upon your level. <br>
<br>
If you are hunting solo for experience, mobs must be within 4 levels or 30% of your current level in order for you to get any from them. For a level 5, he would gain experience from mobs level 2 and up, but not level 1 mobs. For a level 27, he or she would gain experience from fighting mobs level 18 and up. This may be modified slightly for mobs within dungeons, casters, and mobs with other 'special' attacks (poison &amp; disease, hasted, etc)<br>
<br>
Character Levels 1 - 6 <br>
<br>
Green: -4 and below - looks like a reasonably safe opponent <br>
Blue: -1 to -3 - looks like you would have the upper hand <br>
Black/White: even - looks like an even fight <br>
Yellow: +1 and +2 - looks like quite a gamble <br>
Red: +3 and up - what would you like your tombstone to say? <br>
<br>
Character Levels 7 - 12 <br>
<br>
Green: -4 and below - looks like a reasonably safe opponent <br>
Blue: -1 to -3 - looks kind of risky, but you might win <br>
Black/White: even - looks kind of risky..you might win <br>
Yellow: +1 and +2 - looks like quite a gamble <br>
Red: +3 and up - what would you like your tombstone to say? <br>
<br>
Character Levels 13 - 14 <br>
<br>
Green: -6 and below - looks like a reasonably safe opponent <br>
Blue: -4 and -5 - looks like you would have the upper hand <br>
Blue: -1 to -3 - looks kind of risky, but you might win <br>
Black/White: even - looks kind of risky..you might win <br>
Yellow: +1 and +2 - looks like quite a gamble <br>
Red: +3 and up - what would you like your tombstone to say? <br>
<br>
Character Levels 15 - 24 <br>
<br>
Green: -6 or less - looks like a reasonably safe opponent.<br>
Blue: -5 - You would probably win this fight, it's not certain though.<br>
Blue: -4 - looks quite risky, but might be worth a try.<br>
Blue: -3 - looks quit risky.<br>
Blue: -2 and -1 - looks kind of dangerous.<br>
Black/White: same - he appears to be quite formidable. <br>
Yellow: +1 and +2 - looks like quite a gamble <br>
Red: +3 or more - what would you like your tombstone to say?<br>
<br>
Character Levels 25 - 34 <br>
<br>
Green: -11 or more - you could probably win this fight. <br>
Green: -8 to -10 - this creature could pose problems, you would probably defeat it. <br>
Blue: -1 to -7 - appears to be quite formidable. <br>
Black/White: same - looks like quite a gamble. <br>
Yellow: +1 and +2 - looks like it would wipe the floor with you! <br>
Red: +3 or more - what would you like your tombstone to say? <br>
<br>
Character Levels 35 - 40 <br>
<br>
Green: -11 or more - you could probably win this fight. <br>
Green: -10 - this creature could pose problems, you would probably defeat it. <br>
Blue: -1 to -9 - appears to be quite formidable. <br>
Black/White: same - looks like quite a gamble. <br>
Yellow: +1 and +2 - looks like it would wipe the floor with you! <br>
Red: +3 or more - what would you like your tombstone to say? <br>
<br>
* Character levels 41 - 44? <br>
<br>
Green: -12 or more - you could probably win this fight. <br>
Blue: -1 to -11 - appears to be quite formidable. <br>
Black/White: same - looks like quite a gamble. <br>
Yellow: +1 and +2 - looks like it would wipe the floor with you! <br>
Red: +3 or more - what would you like your tombstone to say <br>
<br>
* Character levels 45 - 49? <br>
<br>
Green: -13 or more - you could probably win this fight. <br>
Blue: -1 to -12 - appears to be quite formidable. <br>
Black/White: same - looks like quite a gamble. <br>
Yellow: +1 and +2 - looks like it would wipe the floor with you! <br>
Red: +3 or more - what would you like your tombstone to say?<br>
